==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wistaria
<hw>Wis*ta"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<ety>[So named after <person>Caspar <etsep>Wistar</etsep></person>, an
American anatomist.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of climbing
leguminous plants bearing long, pendulous clusters of pale bluish
flowers. Now commonly spelled <asp>Wisteria</asp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The species commonest in cultivation is the
<spn>Wistaria Sinensis</spn> from Eastern Asia. <spn>Wistaria
fruticosa</spn> grows wild in the southern parts of the United
States.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wisteria</ent>⟦br⟧
